-- Biden Spoke With Ecuador’s President About Snowden, Rhodes Says
-- B y   J u l i a n n a   G o l d m a n
-- 2013-06-29T17:52:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-29/biden-spoke-with-ecuador-s-president-about-snowden-rhodes-says.html
U.S. Vice President  Joe Biden  has
spoken with Ecuador’s President Rafael Correa on a range of
issues including former U.S. intelligence contractor Edward Snowden, according Deputy National Security Advisor  Ben Rhodes .  Rhodes didn’t provide additional details. Correa in his
weekly broadcast on public radio said Biden told him Snowden is
a fugitive from U.S. justice and asked Ecuador to reject
Snowden’s request for asylum. Correa said he told Biden that the
U.S. hasn’t honored Ecuadorean extradition requests in the past.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Julianna Goldman in Washington at 
